## 8. New Required Patterns

### 8.1 EmptyState Pattern
```tsx
// PF6 Pattern
<EmptyState
  headingLevel="h4"
  icon={CubesIcon}
  titleText="Empty state title"
  headerClassName="optional-class"
>
  <EmptyStateBody>Body content</EmptyStateBody>
  <EmptyStateFooter>
    <EmptyStateActions>
      <Button variant="primary">Action</Button>
    </EmptyStateActions>
  </EmptyStateFooter>
</EmptyState>
```

### 8.2 Button with Icons
```tsx
// PF6: Icons must use the icon prop
<Button variant="plain" icon={<TimesIcon />} />
<Button variant="primary" icon={<PlusIcon />}>Add item</Button>
```

### 8.3 Content (replacing Text)
```tsx
// PF6: Single Content component replaces all Text variants
<Content>
  <Content component="h1">Heading</Content>
  <Content component="p">Paragraph</Content>
  <Content component="ul">
    <Content component="li">Item</Content>
  </Content>
</Content>
```

### 8.4 Modal (New Implementation)
```tsx
// PF6: New Modal API (promoted from /next)
import { Modal } from '@patternfly/react-core';
// The new Modal uses a different API than the deprecated one
```

### 8.5 Chart Imports
```tsx
// PF6: Must use /victory subpath
import { Chart, ChartArea, ChartBar } from '@patternfly/react-charts/victory';
```

### 8.6 PageSection
```tsx
// PF6: Only "default" or "secondary" variants
<PageSection variant="default">...</PageSection>
<PageSection variant="secondary">...</PageSection>
// NOT: variant="light", variant="dark", variant="darker"
```

---

## 9. Breakpoint Changes

PF6 uses **rem units** instead of pixels for breakpoints.

| Breakpoint | Design Token | PF5 (px) | PF6 (rem) |
|------------|-------------|----------|-----------|
| xs | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--xs` | 0px | 0rem |
| sm | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--sm` | 576px | 36rem |
| md | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--md` | 768px | 48rem |
| lg | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--lg` | 992px | 62rem |
| xl | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--xl` | 1200px | 75rem |
| 2xl | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--2xl` | 1450px | 90.625rem |

**Action Required:** If you have pixel-based breakpoint logic, divide by 16 to get rem values.

---

## 10. Test Failure Guidance

### Button Tests
1. **`aria-disabled` not found**: PF6 Button with `isDisabled` sets `disabled` attribute, not `aria-disabled` (except when `component` is not "button"). Remove tests that expect `aria-disabled` to be false or match `isDisabled`.
2. **`byText` not finding button attributes**: Button text is now wrapped in a `<span>`. Use `byRole('button', { name: 'text' })` instead of `byText`.

### Select Tests
1. **`Cannot find role`** (React Testing Library): Menu options may not be found if Popper menu is `aria-disabled`. Pass `{hidden: true}` option or change `appendTo` to `inline`.

---

## 11. Codemods Reference

### Main Codemods Suite
```bash
# Dry run (identify issues)
npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest <path> --v6

# Apply fixes
npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest <path> --v6 --fix

# Final cleanup (run ONCE after all other codemods)
npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest <path> --v6 --only data-codemods-cleanup
```

### Class Name Updater
```bash
npx @patternfly/class-name-updater <path> --v6 --fix
```
- Replaces `pf-v5` prefixes with `pf-v6`
- Simple find-and-replace — watch for false positives

### Tokens Update
```bash
# Included in main codemods suite
# Updates global CSS variables and React tokens in .js/.tsx files
```
- Color variables → `--pf-t--temp--dev--tbd` (hot pink) for manual replacement
- Other globals (spacers, fonts, shadows) → auto-fixed to closest match

### CSS Vars Updater
```bash
npx @patternfly/css-vars-updater <path>
```
- Updates CSS variables in .css, .scss, .md files
- Not for React files (use tokens-update for those)

