  <ul class="verdict-reasons">
    <li><strong>10 migration areas addressed</strong> by semver vs <strong>2</strong> by codemods</li>
    <li><strong>Zero remaining pf-v5</strong> CSS class references in semver; <strong>3 remain</strong> in codemods</li>
    <li><strong>Zero deprecated imports</strong> in semver; <strong>7 deprecated shims</strong> introduced by codemods</li>
    <li><strong>Dependency alignment</strong>: React 17→18, Console SDK 1→4, code-editor 5→6 &mdash; only in semver</li>
    <li><strong>Both branches build</strong> successfully with 0 errors</li>
    <li><strong>E2E tests updated</strong> for PF6 DOM structure only in semver</li>
    <li>Semver uses proper PF6 APIs (ModalHeader, EmptyState string titleText) rather than deprecated shims</li>
  </ul>
</div>

