<h2 id="detailed">🔍 Detailed Analysis</h2>

<!-- 6a. Package Upgrades -->
<details>
  <summary>📦 Package / Dependency Upgrades &nbsp; <span class="badge badge-green">semver wins</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h4>What PF6 Requires</h4>
    <p>PatternFly 6 migration guide requires updating <strong>all</strong> <code>@patternfly/*</code> packages to v6, and recommends React 18. The <code>@patternfly/react-code-editor</code> on main was still at v5.</p>

    <h4>Before (main)</h4>
<pre><code>"@openshift-console/dynamic-plugin-sdk": "^1.6.0"
"@patternfly/react-code-editor": "^5.4.0"  // ← PF5!
"react": "^17.0.1"
"react-dom": "^17.0.1"
"@types/react": "^17.0.37"</code></pre>

    <h4>Branch Comparison</h4>
    <table>
      <tr>
        <th>Package</th>
        <th>pf-codemods</th>
        <th>semver/goose</th>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>@openshift-console/dynamic-plugin-sdk</code></td>
        <td><span class="metric-bad">^1.6.0 (unchanged)</span></td>
        <td><span class="metric-good">^4.21.0 ✓</span></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>react</code> / <code>react-dom</code></td>
        <td><span class="metric-bad">^17.0.1 (unchanged)</span></td>
        <td><span class="metric-good">^18.3.1 ✓</span></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>@types/react</code></td>
        <td><span class="metric-bad">^17.0.37 (unchanged)</span></td>
        <td><span class="metric-good">^18.3.0 ✓</span></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>@patternfly/react-code-editor</code></td>
        <td><span class="metric-bad">^5.4.0 (unchanged, PF5!)</span></td>
        <td><span class="metric-good">^6.4.1 ✓</span></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>react-router-dom-v5-compat</code></td>
        <td><span class="metric-neutral">Not added</span></td>
        <td><span class="metric-good">^6.30.4 (added)</span></td>
      </tr>
    </table>

    <p><strong>Verdict:</strong> Codemods made <strong>zero</strong> dependency changes. Semver aligned all packages including the critical React 17→18 upgrade, console SDK major version bump, and the remaining PF5 code-editor package.</p>
    <p><strong>Note on scope:</strong> The React 18 + SDK 4.x upgrades go beyond pure PF6 migration, but they are <em>recommended</em> by the PF6 upgrade guide and required for full compatibility with PF6's concurrent features. The <code>react-router-dom-v5-compat</code> addition is forward-looking but not strictly PF6-required. A small scope penalty applies.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- 6b. EmptyState -->
<details>
  <summary>🔲 EmptyState Component Migration &nbsp; <span class="badge badge-green">semver wins</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h4>What Changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>PF6 removes <code>EmptyStateHeader</code> and <code>EmptyStateIcon</code> as separate components. The <code>titleText</code> prop now accepts a <strong>plain string</strong>, and <code>headingLevel</code> / <code>icon</code> are direct props on <code>EmptyState</code>.</p>

    <h4>Before (main) — 8 instances across 6 files</h4>
<pre><code>&lt;EmptyState
  titleText={
    &lt;Title headingLevel="h4" size="lg"&gt;
      {t('Access Denied')}
    &lt;/Title&gt;
  }
  icon={LockIcon}
&gt;</code></pre>

    <h4>After — pf-codemods</h4>
<pre><code>// ❌ NO CHANGES — identical to main
// All 8 EmptyState instances still wrap titleText in &lt;Title&gt;</code></pre>

    <h4>After — semver/goose (all 8 instances fixed)</h4>
<pre><code>&lt;EmptyState
  titleText={t('Access Denied')}
  headingLevel="h4"
  icon={LockIcon}
&gt;</code></pre>

    <p><strong>Files migrated by semver:</strong> <code>KuadrantOverviewPage.tsx</code> (4), <code>ResourceList.tsx</code> (1), <code>NoPermissionsView.tsx</code> (1), <code>AssociatedResourceList.tsx</code> (1), <code>APIProductDefinitionTab.tsx</code> (1), <code>APIProductPoliciesTab.tsx</code> (2). Unused <code>Title</code> imports cleaned up from 5 files.</p>
    <p><strong>Verdict:</strong> Codemods missed this entirely. Semver properly applied the PF6 EmptyState API across all instances.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- 6c. Modal -->
<details>
  <summary>📋 Modal Component Migration &nbsp; <span class="badge badge-green">semver wins</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h4>What Changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>The old Modal (with <code>title</code> prop) was deprecated. PF6 promotes the new Modal from <code>/next</code> which uses <code>&lt;ModalHeader&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;ModalBody&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;ModalFooter&gt;</code> child composition. The old Modal is available via <code>@patternfly/react-core/deprecated</code> as a temporary bridge.</p>

    <h4>Branch Comparison</h4>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Aspect</th><th>pf-codemods</th><th>semver/goose</th></tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Approach</td>
        <td><span class="metric-bad">Moved imports to <code>/deprecated</code></span></td>
        <td><span class="metric-good">Full migration to new Modal API</span></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Modal + ModalVariant import</td>
        <td><code>from '@patternfly/react-core/deprecated'</code></td>
        <td><code>from '@patternfly/react-core'</code> (new API)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>title prop</td>
        <td>Still uses <code>title={...}</code> (old API)</td>
        <td>Replaced with <code>&lt;ModalHeader title={...} /&gt;</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Files affected</td>
        <td>7 files</td>
        <td>7 files</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Tech debt</td>
        <td><span class="metric-bad">Accumulates — deprecated API will be removed</span></td>
        <td><span class="metric-good">Clean — uses target API</span></td>
      </tr>
    </table>

    <h4>pf-codemods example (AddLimitModal.tsx)</h4>
<pre><code>// Imports moved to deprecated path
import { Modal, ModalVariant } from '@patternfly/react-core/deprecated';
// Usage unchanged — still uses old title prop
&lt;Modal title={t('Add Limit')} variant={ModalVariant.medium}&gt;</code></pre>

    <h4>semver/goose example (AddLimitModal.tsx)</h4>
<pre><code>// Imports from main path (new API)
import { Modal, ModalHeader, ModalBody, ModalFooter } from '@patternfly/react-core';
// Uses new compositional API
&lt;Modal isOpen={...} onClose={...}&gt;
  &lt;ModalHeader title={t('Add Limit')} /&gt;
  &lt;ModalBody&gt;...&lt;/ModalBody&gt;
  &lt;ModalFooter&gt;...&lt;/ModalFooter&gt;
&lt;/Modal&gt;</code></pre>

    <p><strong>Verdict:</strong> Codemods took the minimal "deprecated shim" approach. Semver did the full migration to the new PF6 Modal API. The codemods approach is valid as a stepping stone but introduces tech debt; the deprecated API will eventually be removed.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- 6d. CSS Classes -->
<details>
  <summary>🎨 CSS Class Prefix Migration &nbsp; <span class="badge badge-green">semver wins</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h4>What Changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>All PatternFly CSS classes changed prefix: <code>.pf-v5-c-*</code> → <code>.pf-v6-c-*</code>, <code>.pf-v5-l-*</code> → <code>.pf-v6-l-*</code>, etc.</p>

    <h4>Instances on main (ResourceList.tsx)</h4>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Line</th><th>PF5 Class</th><th>pf-codemods</th><th>semver/goose</th></tr>
      <tr>
        <td>~201</td>
