<!-- 6i. E2E Tests -->
<details>
  <summary>🧪 E2E Test Updates for PF6 DOM &nbsp; <span class="badge badge-green">semver wins</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h4>What Changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>PF6 changed dropdown/menu DOM structure: items are now <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> elements instead of <code>role="menuitem"</code>, and disabled state uses the native <code>disabled</code> attribute rather than <code>aria-disabled</code>.</p>

    <table>
      <tr><th>Pattern</th><th>Before (PF5)</th><th>After (PF6, semver)</th></tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Menu item selection</td>
        <td><code>[role="menuitem"]:has-text(...)</code></td>
        <td><code>li:has-text(...)</code> / <code>getByText(...)</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Disabled assertion</td>
        <td><code>getAttribute('aria-disabled')</code></td>
        <td><code>toBeDisabled()</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Enabled assertion</td>
        <td><code>getAttribute('aria-disabled') === null</code></td>
        <td><code>toBeEnabled()</code></td>
      </tr>
    </table>

    <p><strong>pf-codemods:</strong> No E2E test changes. <strong>semver:</strong> Comprehensive update of all Playwright selectors and assertions in <code>rbac.spec.ts</code>.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- 6j. Webpack Config -->
<details>
  <summary>⚙️ Webpack Configuration &nbsp; <span class="badge badge-green">semver wins</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h4>semver/goose change</h4>
<pre><code>// Before
new ConsoleRemotePlugin()

// After
new ConsoleRemotePlugin({ validateSharedModules: false })</code></pre>
    <p>This is <strong>critical</strong> for the React 18 + Console SDK 4.x upgrade. The stricter shared module validation in SDK 4.x would fail due to major version mismatches between the plugin's PF6 modules and the host console's shared modules. <code>pf-codemods</code> did not need this change because it didn't upgrade those dependencies.</p>
  </div>
</details>

